    <refnamediv>
        <refname>gl_WorkGroupID</refname>
        <refpurpose>contains the index of the workgroup currently being operated on by a compute shader</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsynopsisdiv>
        <title>Declaration</title>
        <fieldsynopsis>
            <modifier>in</modifier> 
            <type>uvec3</type> 
            <varname>gl_WorkGroupID</varname>
        </fieldsynopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>
    <refsect1 xml:id="description"><title>Description</title>
        <para>
            In the compute language, <varname>gl_WorkGroupID</varname>
            contains the 3-dimensional index of the global work group 
            that the current compute shader invocation is executing within. The possible values range
            across the parameters passed into <function>glDispatchCompute</function>, i.e., from (0, 0, 0) to
            (<varname>gl_NumWorkGroups.x</varname> - 1, <varname>gl_NumWorkGroups.y</varname> - 1, <varname>gl_NumWorkGroups.z</varname> - 1).
        </para>
    </refsect1>
